The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Bike lifted, goons lynched
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bike lifted, goons lynched
          FARHANA KALAM                              
	Gaya, Oct. 12: Three youths were meted out instant justice in a Sherghati village last night when they tried to escape after snatching a motorcycle and cash from a villager.        
	According to reports reaching the district headquarters, one villager in Sheikhpura, about 35km from here, also sustained gunshot injury as in their bid to escape, the road robbers fired to scare away the villagers.         
	While two of the robbers died on the spot, the third one succumbed to his injuries at Anugrah Narain Magadh Medical College.         
	Kailu Yadav, the villager who received gunshot injury and was admitted to the medical college also, is said to be out of danger.         
	Mukesh Kumar, a resident of Jehanabad, was going to his in-laws place in Sheikhpura, when armed robbers snatched his motorcycle (no. BR18-1272). The robbers also snatched Rs 3,000 from Mukesh, who subsequently raised alarm and the villagers cornered the road robbers. One of the robbers fired from his country-made gun injuring Kailu. Within a few minutes, the villagers lynched the robbers, killing two of them  Shahid Khan of Dumaria, Shambhu Paswan of Amas  on the spot. Kashi alias Mughal died later at the hospital.        
	Gaya superintendent of police Mallar Vizhi said that the matter was being investigated and the identity of the people who lynched the robbers was not known.         
	Kidnap bid foiled        
	Residents of the Chand Chauraha area in Gaya foiled an attempt to kidnap the owner of a watch showroom late on Saturday evening.         
	One of the residents, who had foiled the kidnapping for ransom attempt, was injured when the criminals fired at him. A case was lodged at the Civil Lines police station.                                                                                                                                                                         
